article_title: 400,000 Citizens To Lose Health Insurance (Again) Because Of Obamacare Co-Op Failures

article_metadata.author: Grace-Marie Turner

og.description: Latest ObamaCare co-op failures means 51,000 citizens in Kentucky will be forced to find new health insurance for 2016, bringing to 400,000 the number of people impacted by the failures of this experiment in citizen-run health insurance companies costing taxpayers $2.4 billion.
